# Flipper Riverpod performance

Read **`docs/riverpod_perf.md`** for regression tests and tracing. Apply these rules when adding or changing providers/widgets in Flipper.

## Mental model

Riverpod slowness here is usually **rebuild fan-out** and **too many Ditto observers**, not Riverpod itself. Ditto/Capella I/O runs on the **main isolate** — you cannot fix that with `compute()`. Win by: fewer watches, narrower rebuilds, batched streams, paged data.

```
Bad:  N widgets × stockByVariantProvider(id)     → N Ditto observers
Good: stocksForVisibleVariantsProvider(page)    → 1 observer, pass Stock? into rows

Bad:  ref.watch(pendingTransactionStreamProvider) → whole checkout rebuilds
Good: ref.watch(pending...select((a) => a.asData?.value.customerId))
```

## Provider design

- **One stream hub, derive in memory** — e.g. `coreTransactionsStream` + filter; avoid duplicate Ditto subscriptions for the same query args.
- **Page-scoped data for paged UIs** — reports: SQL `LIMIT`/`OFFSET` for transactions; scope PLU/items to **current page sale ids**, not full `dateRange`.
- **Batch at list level** — payment sums (`getPaymentSumsByTransactionIdsChunked`), stocks (`watchStocksByIds`), tickets (`openPosTicketsTransactionsStream` with `status IN (...)`).
- **`ref.listen` for side effects** — cache sync, reconciliation (`posCartStreamReconciliationProvider`); do not `watch` these in widgets.
- **`select()` on every derived UI field** — cart count, selection boolean, customer id, agent id.
- **`keepAlive` sparingly** — report snapshot/page index while screen mounted; default stay `autoDispose`.
- **Codegen** — new providers in `packages/flipper_models/lib/providers/` with `@riverpod`; avoid growing `riverpod_states.dart`.
- **Riverpod 3** — `StateProvider` from `package:flutter_riverpod/legacy.dart`; `ProviderBase` from `package:flutter_riverpod/misc.dart`.

## Widget design

- **Split `Consumer` trees** — header/filters separate from list body; payment footer separate from cart lines.
- **Lists** — `ListView.builder` + stable keys; never `ref.watch` full collections inside `itemBuilder` without `select`.
- **Per-row selection** — `ticketSelectionProvider.select((s) => s.contains(id))`, not full `Set` watch on every card.
- **No per-row `FutureBuilder` for DB** — lift batch fetch to parent provider; pass primitives into stateless children.
- **Prefer `invalidate` over `refresh`** on hot paths unless stream re-subscribe is required.

## Preserve (do not regress)

- Cart tap path: `optimisticCartProvider`, `posCartDisplayEpochProvider`, `posCartQtyForVariantProvider`, `posCartStreamReconciliationProvider` via `ref.listen`.
- Budget: `kPosCartTapDisplayMaxMicroseconds` in `pos_cart_sync_tap.dart` — run `pos_cart_tap_sync_perf_test.dart` after cart changes.

## Avoid

- Full-period Ditto streams feeding SQL-paged grids.
- KPI/totals providers `watch`ing live PLU streams (recompute on dedicated SQL or debounced future).
- `talker.info` / `debugPrint` in provider `build` hot paths (e.g. `featureAccess`).
- `providerPerfTracingEnabledProvider` always-on in committed `main.dart` (debug profiling only).
- Duplicate provider names (`searchStringProvider` — POS uses codegen; supplier catalog uses `supplierCatalogSearchProvider`).

## Dev tracing

```dart
// ProviderScope override in main.dart — debug only, do not ship always-on
providerPerfTracingEnabledProvider.overrideWith((ref) => true);
// Or inside any Consumer under ProviderScope:
ref.read(providerPerfTracingEnabledProvider.notifier).state = true;
```

Allowlist: `kProviderPerfTraceAllowlist` in `provider_perf_observer.dart`.

## Remaining hotspots (only if profiling shows jank)

- `QuickSellingView` — many full `pendingTransactionStream` / `posCartDisplayItems` watches; narrow with `select`.
- `dashboardGaugeSnapshotProvider` — 3 streams × 2 periods; consolidate.
- Favorites/alternate grids — pass `stocksById` like `product_view` (fallback still uses `stockByVariantProvider`).
